## Architecture Overview

The pipeline uses a sandboxed collector service (`:collector`) with its own process, communicating via AIDL to a background uploader service. Events are encrypted at rest using SQLCipher + per-event AES-GCM, with governance applied before storage.

### AIDL Contracts

```aidl
// IDataCollector.aidl
package com.example.eventpipeline;

import com.example.eventpipeline.Event;
import com.example.eventpipeline.BatchInfo;

interface IDataCollector {
    /**
     * Collects a single UI event after governance processing.
     * Returns true if event was buffered successfully.
     */
    boolean collectEvent(in Event event);

    /**
     * Flushes all pending events up to the specified batchId.
     * Called by uploader when batch is ready for transmission.
     */
    void flushBatch(long batchId);

    /**
     * Retrieves count of pending events awaiting upload.
     */
    int getPendingEventCount();

    /**
     * Returns metadata about the next batch ready for upload.
     */
    BatchInfo getNextBatchInfo();

    /**
     * Bulk retrieve events for a specific batch.
     */
    List<Event> getBatchEvents(long batchId);

    /**
     * Marks batch as acknowledged by backend (exactly-once handling).
     */
    void acknowledgeBatch(long batchId, boolean success);

    /**
     * Governance: Returns allowed event types for this app version.
     */
    List<String> getAllowedEventTypes();
}
```

```java
// Data models
@Entity(tableName = "events")
